user instructions for Hiarchical NoteBook (hnb):
	command line parameters
		at the time of writing pdb takes only one parameter,
		the file to edit. if this parameter i omitted, hnb
		will load the default file, ( in unix this is $HOME/.hnb)
		
		hnb will display which file is the default file if you
		supply it with an -h or --help option
	navigating/entering data
		you navigate among the entries with cursor keys,
		or by typing the first characthers of the entry data
		by pressing <tab> the entire current node is "typed" in
		pressing tab again will enter the child this alllows 
		rapid searching through the data
		
		if the characthers typed in doesn't match an existing node
		a new node will be created
		 
		a menu at the bottom will at all times tell you what keys
		do what.
	editing existing data
		whith a node selected.. (reversed text) you can press
		return to enter editing mode
		in editing mode, backspace removes text, cursor keys 
		navigate left/right in the data, characters typed will
		be inserted at the current position. return saves the data
		escape will cancel editing
	removing nodes
		pressing delete or backspace while navigating will remove
		a node and all it's children,.. be careful
		I think I must add confirmation if the node contains children
		or perhaps enforce something like ctrl+delete to do a recursive
		deletinion
	saving/quitting
		pressing [esc] will give you the choices to,
		(s)ave
		(q)uit without saving
		(y)save and quit
		(esc) .. abort action
	sorting
		the only nonplaced option,.. at the moment is sort
		which will sort all the siblings of the current
		node alphabetically


psst if this is your first time using hnb, the two periods
after the topmost line, indicates that this entry have children
pressing your right cursor key, will enter the child entries
to choose among sibling entries use the up/down arrows, and
to go back to a parent node press the your left cursor key

